"{\"uid\": \"rte.ie-sport-paris-2024-2024-0801-1463095-paris-2024-irish-in-action-on-day-7-of-olympic-games\", \"text\": \"History beckons for Paul O'Donovan on Day 7 of Paris 2024.  The man from Skibbereen can become the first ever Irish Olympian to medal at three Games if he and Fintan McCarthy can achieve a podium finish in the lightweight double sculls final.  The reigning Olympic champions will be the team to beat at the Vaires-sur-Marne Nautical Stadium on Friday morning.  There will be Irish involvement in no less than five Olympic finals on Friday as a memorable opening week of Paris 2024 comes to a close.  Also taking to the water and hoping for medal success will be Margaret Cremen and Aoife Casey in the women's lightweight double skulls and Ross Corrigan and Nathan Timoney in the men's pair.  Irish sailors Robert Dickson and Sean Waddilove's Olympic medal mission was twice postponed due to a lack of wind in Marseille yesterday.  The Irish duo are second overall and well placed to contend for a place on the podium when the race hopefully resumes at 12.13pm on Friday.  Ireland's showjumpers will compete in the team event final after a fine performance in yesterday's semi-final.  Shane Sweetnam, Daniel Coyle and Cian O'Connor finished in sixth place to comfortably qualify.  Day 7 will also mark the beginning of track-and-field at these Games, with Andrew Coscoran, Luke McCann and Cathal Doyle competing in the men's 1500m heats, which begin just after 10am.  The evening session will see Jodie McCann compete in the Women's 5,000m heats while the mixed 4x400m relay team are also in action.  (In order of start time)  0844Men's singles round 2:Shane Lowry  1106Men's singles round 2:Rory McIlroy  1005-1031Men's 1500m Heats:Andrew Coscoran(Heat 1),Luke McCann(Heat 2) andCathal Doyle(Heat 3)  1710-1754Women's 5000m round 1 Heat 2:Jodie McCann  1810-1826Mixed 4x400m relay Heat 2:Ireland(Team TBC)  1910-1958Men's shot put qualifying Group B:Eric Favors  1014-1035Women's 200m individual medley Heat 5 :Ellen Walshe  2022-2036Women's 200m individual medley semi-finals:Ellen Walshe(if qualified)  1030-1042Men's pair final:Ross CarriganandNathan Twomey  1102-1114Men's lightweight double sculls final:Paul O'DonovanandFintan McCarthy  1122-1134Women's lightweight double sculls final:Margaret CremenandAoife Casey  1110-1206Women's dinghy race 3:Eve McMahon  1218-1314Women's dinghy race 4:Eve McMahon  1430-1526Men's dinghy race 3:Finn Lynch  1538-1634Men's dinghy race 4:Finn Lynch  TBCSkiff medal race:Robert DicksonandSean Waddilove  1300-1500Show jumping team event final:Ireland(Daniel Coyle and Legacy, Cian O'Connor and Maurice, Shane Sweetnam and James Kann Cruz)  1430Women's 57kg (featherweight) -round of 16:Michaela Walshv Svetlana Staneva (BUL)  1430-1527Men's kayak cross time trial:Liam JegouandNoel Hendrick  1540-1637Women's kayak cross time trial:Madison Corcoran  1600Men's Pool B: New Zealand vIreland  \\u00a9 RT\\u00c9 2026. RT\\u00c9.ie is the website of Raidi\\u00f3 Teilif\\u00eds \\u00c9ireann, Ireland's National Public Service Media. RT\\u00c9 is not responsible for the content of external internet sites.  Images Courtesy of Getty Images.\"}"